President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Mississippi due to severe storms, tornadoes, straight-line winds, and flooding that occurred from January 10 to January 11, 2020. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts. The affected counties include Bolivar, Choctaw, Clay, DeSoto, Oktibbeha, Panola, Prentiss, Sunflower, Tishomingo, and Washington. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and statewide hazard mitigation measures. Terry L. Quarles has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Further damage assessments may result in additional designations. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.